Patrick Kluivert wants Aston Villa wing-back Leandro Bacuna to play for Curacao.

Curacao named former Newcastle, Barcelona and Ajax striker Kluivert as national team coach earlier this week and he has sounded out Bacuna about committing to their World Cup qualifying campaign.

Aston Villa wing-back Leandro Bacuna (left) is wanted to play for Curacao by new manager Patrick Kluivert

Bacuna said: 'I was even approached last year. I said then that I wanted to think about, which has actually not changed.

'That Kluivert was added to the staff, of course, gives something extra to the invitation.'

The 23-year-old has made 14 appearances for  Villa this season, scoring once.

